node.text: It was a beautiful day and I’m in love with my new daughter-in-law. Check out this video shot and produced by Stephen Norregaard. See the full wide format version here: https://vimeo.com/308998543

node.text: A couple days ago I posted one end of the kitchen/dining space at our #jsdpaintedbrick project. And today, I’m posting the other end!  Every house needs a cozy spot to sit down together for a meal. Swipe through to see all the angles AND the before!  Light fixtures, table and hardware from @stofferhome Cabinetry is in Natural Oak and Birmingham from @stofferhomecabinetry Photography by @stofferphotographyinteriors and remodeling by @kenowabuilders

node.text: When the formal dining room became the kitchen @johnstoffer and @maurastoffer ‘s “new” house. Make sure you swipe through to see the before! This gorgeous island is a custom design and the range alcove is from @stofferhomecabinetry in Cotswold Green. “Longbridge” pulls available @stofferhome  John sent me a folder with some more great pics and I can’t wait to show them to you!

node.text: We combined the dining room and kitchen in the #jsdpaintedbrick project to make a space where there is plenty of room for the family to hang out together. The kitchen is where everyone ends up. Am I right?? But because we all need a stash space, we used this little corner for a jewel of a walk-in pantry. @stofferhomecabinetry in natural Oak, Birmingham and Cotswold Green. “Monroe” pulls and “Thatcher” knobs, lighting and “Endeavor” art from @stofferhome

node.text: I love this whole set up at The Madison!  The interior windows were old storm windows on the sun porch and repurposed here. The millwork was patiently restored and replaced by @kenowabuilders using material from @the_empire_co  There really are true craftsmen out there, and I feel so grateful they worked at The Madison where I can enjoy the fruit of their labor every day. Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors Light fixture from @stofferhome

node.text: The family room at The Madison was very fun to put together. I love the mix of furniture, art, lighting and things I’ve collected over the years. It feels like home. Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors Remodeling by @kenowabuilders most furniture, lighting and accessories are from @stofferhome  Wing back chairs from @rejuvenation

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jean Stoffer in Grand Rapids, Michigan. May be an image of grass and tree.

node.text: Would ya look at what I just found!  A great old house in need.  I might have to get involved. Actually, I just bought it! 😍 Anybody ready to join me for a slow flip?  I’ll be trying out some new things in this old beauty. What would you guys like to see first?  UPDATE!  Going live today (7/4) at 4 pm Eastern with a walk through!
